                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1779" notAfter="1800">According to the colophon, the Ms.
                        was written during the reign of king Takla Giyorgis (Takla Giyorgis I, r.
                        1779-84, 1788-89, 1794-95, 1795-96, 1798-99, 1800 A.D.).</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>Additio 3 mentions Walda Gabǝr as the one who
                     donated the book to the church of Māryām Ṣäbäla. His name is also written in
                     the supplication formulas over an erased name, e.g., on 5ra, 56va, 101va, 112rb, 139ra.
 The names of his relatives are
                     also written in the supplication formulas over an erased name: his wife Walatta
                     Bǝʾsitu (e.g., 5ra, 37rb, 102ra, 131va, 142rb),
                     his father Walda Muse (5ra, 148vb). The names of Habta Giyorgis and Walatta
                     Māryām are written in the main hand in the supplication formulas on 141rb, 142ra. They are possibly the names of the
                     former owners.</provenance></history>
